<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1891,2024]" pageId="17" pageNumber="312">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,468,1891,1916]" pageId="17" pageNumber="312">Skeletal arrangement.</emphasis>
Choanosomal skeleton composed by bundles of oxeas protriaenes and anatriaenes spirally arranged from the central part toward the periphery. Auxiliary oxeas either disposed in palisade at the sponge periphery or scattered in the choanosomal zone. Trichodal protriaenes distributed at the peripheral zone; sigmaspires spread through the sponge. Anatrianes III form part of the dense hair-like surface tufts.
</paragraph>
